    • Method Detail

      • storeFormatStart

        public final void storeFormatStart(PPLZStorage storageType,
                                   java.lang.String name)
                            throws BarcodePrinterIllegalArgumentException,
                                   BarcodePrinterGeneralException
        This function is used to create and start a 'Format', and this function should be used in pair with storeFormatEnd.
        Parameters:
        storageType - [in] Location of storage device. Use PPLZStorage enum to set up.
        name - [in] The 'Format' name to create. Range: 1~8 alphanumeric (alphabets or numbers) characters.
        Throws:
        BarcodePrinterIllegalArgumentException - Invalid parameter or parameter is out of the valid range.
        BarcodePrinterGeneralException - General error, byte array operation error.

        If not used in pair with storeFormatEnd, unexpected errors will occur, please be cautious when using this.

        This function only create and download 'Format', then store the content of 'Format' into the printer's storage device. No printing or deleting the 'Format' will be executed.

        Hence, if want to execute (print), please call printStoreFormat; if want to delete, please call deleteStoreFormat.

        As Flash memory has a limited access lifespan, unless 'Format' is to be repeatedly used, it is recommended to store the 'Format' in DRAM.

        See Also:
        PPLZStorage, storeFormatEnd(), printStoreFormat(com.argox.sdk.barcodeprinter.emulation.pplz.PPLZStorage, java.lang.String), deleteStoreFormat(com.argox.sdk.barcodeprinter.emulation.pplz.PPLZStorage, java.lang.String)

        public final void deleteStoreFormat(PPLZStorage storageType,
                                    java.lang.String name)
                             throws BarcodePrinterIllegalArgumentException,
                                    BarcodePrinterGeneralException
        This function is used to delete the 'Format' stored in the printer.
        Parameters:
        storageType - [in] Location of storage device. Use PPLZStorage enum to set up.
        name - [in] The 'Format' name to delete. If the "*" string is used, all 'Format' will be deleted. Range: 1~8 English letters or numbers (alphanumeric) characters or asterisks (asterisk).
        Throws:
        BarcodePrinterIllegalArgumentException - Invalid parameter or parameter is out of the valid range.
        BarcodePrinterGeneralException - General error, byte array operation error.
        See Also:
